The whole of the Corps Diplomatique at present in London waited upon Earl Granville at the Foreign Office yesterday .
The Right Hon . W. E. Gladstone has left the Castle . The Duchess of Argyll visited the Queen and Princess Louise on Monday .

The Prince of Wales , attended by Major Grey , visited the Convict Establishment at Portland yesterday , when his Royal Highness was conducted through the establishment by Mr. Clifton ( the Governor ) and the various officers of the prison .

The Prince of Wales presided on Thursday , at Marl borough - house , at a meeting of Her Majesty's Commis sioners for the Exhibition of 1851 , held for the purpose of receiving the President and Vice - President of the Commission appointed by the Emperor of the French to co - operate in carrying out the International Exhibition of 1871. There were present at the meeting - M . Ozeme ( the President ) and M. du Sommerard ( the Vice - President ) , of the French Commission ; Earl Granville , Mr. Gladstone , Sir Charles Lyell , Sir Roderick Murchison , Sir Francis Grant , Sir Francis Sandford , Mr. T. Baring , Mr. E. Bowring , Mr. T. Fairbairn , Mr. Gibson , Dr. Lyon Playfair , Mr. Thring , Mr. Vignolles , and Lieutenant - Colonel Scott ( Secretary ) . Mr. Cole attended the meeting .

The Prince of Wales , attended by Lord Alfred Hervey , Major Grey , and Mr. Fisher , went to the Agricultural - kall , Islington , on Saturday , and opened the Workmen's Inter national Exhibition on behalf of Her Majesty the Queen .

Her Majesty the Queen , their Royal Highuesses Princes Beatrice , Prince Leopold , and Prince Christian attended Divino service this morning in the private ohupel . The Very Rev , the Deau of Chester preached the sermon .

Their Majesties were conducted to the School Library , and after signing the Minute Book of the School and the Visitors ' Book of the Students ' Union , were conducted to Their carriage and returned to the Palace . Vice - Admiral the Prince of Jumbara ( Head of the Siamese Naval Mission ) , and General the Prince of Kambaeng Bejra ( Commissioner General of Railways of Siam ) and the Princess of Kambaeng Bejra visited The King and Queen and remained to Luncheon . Queen Amélie visited Their Majesties this t afternoon .

Queen Amélie visited Their Majesties this t afternoon .

A Royal salute was fired upon Their Majesties ' arrival by the 1st Welsh Brigade , Royal Field Artillery , Territorial Army , under the command of Major B. R. Benyon Winsor . The Mayor of Swansea had the honour of being presented to The King and Queen , and afterwards presented the Mayoress ( Miss Sinclair ) , the Recorder , and the Town Clerk . The Mayoress had the honour of presenting bouquets to The Queen and the Princess Mary . An address was presented to The King from the County Borough , Swansea , to which His

The whole of the Corps Diplomatique at present in London waited upon Earl Granville at the Foreign Office yesterday .

This evening the Lieutenant - Governor of the Isle of Man and Mrs. Fry , the Bishop of Sodor and Man and Mrs. Denton Thompson , the First Deemster and Mrs. Stevenson Moore , the Second Deemster and Mrs. Cheslyn Callow , the Attorney - General and Mrs. Ring , the Speaker of the House of Keys and Mrs. Clucas , and the Government Secretary and Mrs. Bertram Sargeaunt had the honour of being invited to dinner with their Majesties , but were unavoid ably prevented from obeying their Majesties ' command on account of the Royal yacht having left Douglas Bay .

Earl de Grey and Ripon , Lord President of the Council , gave a dinner at his residence in Carlton - gardens on Wed nesday evening , at which the Roll of Sheriffs for the coun ties of England and Wales for the present year was settled . The company included the Chancellor , Viscount Sydney , the Right Hon . W. E. Gladstone , M.P. , the Earl of Kim berley , the Right Hon . H. A. Bruce , M.P. , the Earl of Clarendon , the Right Hon . text: Prince Christian , attended by Lieutenant - Colonel George G. Gordon , dined with Colonel Aitchison and the officers of the 2d Battalion Scots Fusilier Guards , at the Infantry Barracks , Windsor , last evening .
The Earl of Morley and the Hon . Algernon W. F. Gre ville have succeeded the Earl of Camperdown and Colonel Lynedoch Gardiner as Lord and Groom in Waiting .

The Hon . Douglas and the Lady Constance Cairns , Sir Robert and Lady Lorimer , the Very Revd . Sir George and Lady Adam Smith , Colonel A. B. E. Cator ( commanding Scots Guards ) , Major Sir Victor Mackenzie , Bt . , Major E. C. T. Warner , Major H. O. E. Ross , and Captain the Lord Carnegie ( Scots Guards ) had the honour of dining with The King and Queen this evening .

The King and Queen , accompanied by the Princess Mary , also the Princess Royal , with Princess Maud , Queen Amélie , and Prince Axel of Denmark , visited Queen Alexandra to - day and remained to luncheon .
Civil Hospital Reserve . - Miss Florence BROOME ( also received the Military Medal ) .

The Queen was graciously pleased to accept the Honorary Degree of Doctor of Laws , for which Her Majesty was presented by the Dean of the Faculty of Law , and the degree was con ferred by the Vice - Chancellor ..

The Earl Curzon of Kedleston ( Secretary or State for Foreign Affairs ) was present , and had an audience of The King , and the Earl of Onslow ( Lord in Waiting ) , the Master of the Household , Major - General Sir John Hanbury Williams ( Marshal of the Diplomatic Corps ) , Sir Edward Wallington and Captain Sir Charles Cust , Bt . , R.N. ( Groom and Equerry in Wait ing ) , and the Deputy - Master of the Household were in attendance .

MARLBOROUGH HOUSE , Nov. 12 . General the Right Hon . Sir Dighton Probyn ( Comptroller to Queen Alexandra ) represented Her Majesty at the Memorial Service for Colonel Sir James Gildea , Chairman of the Soldiers ' and Sailors ' Families Association , which took place at St. Jude's Church , Courtfield Gardens , S.W. , to - day .
